<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2019-02-12</DATELINE><TITLE>Bilateral phacoemulsification and intraocular lens implantation in a young African lion (Panthera leo)</TITLE><BODY>An 18-month-old intact female lioness (Panthera leo) was referred to the Clinica Veterinaria Roma Sud for evaluation of bilateral cataracts. Phacoemulsification and implantation of +30 diopter intraocular lens (IOL) were performed bilaterally. Seven years after surgery, the IOL remained centrally positioned and the patient had normal activity.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>